<h2 id="internship-experience">Internship Experience</h2>

<h3 id="audio-rd-intern">Audio R&amp;D Intern</h3>
<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">June 2020 - Sept 2020</code>
Qualcomm, Multimedia R&amp;D Team - Redmond, Washington (Remote)</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Researched</strong> methods of minimizing audio motion latency in interactive experiences to provide a more enjoyable and responsive experience for the listener.</li>
  <li><strong>Prototyped</strong> new spatial audio streaming technologies to bring high-quality immersive audio experiences to a wider consumer audience.</li>
  <li><strong>Developed</strong> a custom end-to-end audio experience in C++ and JavaScript to demonstrate the viability of the prototyped technologies.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="audio-programming-intern">Audio Programming Intern</h3>
<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">May 2019 - Aug 2019</code>
Tsugi Studio - Niigata, Japan</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Built</strong> an application in C# to dynamically generate and compile C++ software for 3 different platforms.</li>
  <li><strong>Optimized</strong> C++ DSP Code to achieve a performance increase of ~4900% via Data Oriented Design and SIMD assembly intrinsics.</li>
  <li><strong>Ported</strong> C# DSP objects into C++.</li>
  <li><strong>Wrote</strong> a C/C++ Fast Fourier Transform capable of using a 4096-byte window in real-time.</li>
</ul>

